narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned an extensive history and overview of the United States Navy, including traditions, customs and courtesies, specific historic individuals, and common practices and daily life today. Broadened our understanding of the Navy, a life working and serving in the Navy, and the specifics which we would need to know to work in the fleet.
Basic principles of being a midshipman and understanding the structure and roles of different units in the navy and marine corps.
I learned about the Military, with a focus on the United States Navy's functions and chain of command.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think a big strength of this class was that the quizzes and exams were straight forward. I knew exactly what would be on them, and so I was able to properly prepare.

The strengths of this course are the Professor and the stories he is able to tell to elaborate upon material being discussed. The more we can hear about first hand experiences relevant to the material the better.
Strong course, well laid out. Class sessions were long, however it was manageable.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Although this course is geared mostly towards Navy Midshipmen preparing to join the Navy, it would be a stimulating class for any student.
Yes! Not only NROTC but anyone interested in the Navy!
